node.text:
Times like these make me think even deeper about the ones that came before us. What we have to endure now, they’ve endured tenfold. And I’m so thankful. The strength and poise is really unmatched. They paved the way. Fought the way. Sometimes peacefully and sometimes rightfully not. I am fueled with hope and filled with pride watching videos like this-just as much as the recent ones being posted. We are tired but we continuously get up because we know our worth and right. Though our color is such a huge part of our divide, pain and tragedies.. I would still choose to be BLACK over and over and over again. Thank you to our brothers and sisters fighting now AND then. The power we hold is stronger than any other. 
stay safe.
